    import cv2
    import numpy as np
    import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

    img_path = r"C:\water.jpg"
    img = cv2.imread(img_path, cv2.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)

    if img is None:
    raise FileNotFoundError("Image file not found. Check the path.")

    def contrast_stretching(image):
    min_val = np.min(image)
    max_val = np.max(image)
    stretched = (image - min_val) * (255 / (max_val - min_val))
    return np.uint8(stretched)

    stretched_img = contrast_stretching(img)
    hist_eq_img = cv2.equalizeHist(img)

    def plot_images_and_histograms(images, titles):
    plt.figure(figsize=(15,10))
    for i, (image, title) in enumerate(zip(images, titles), 1):
    plt.subplot(3, 2, 2*i - 1)
    plt.imshow(image, cmap='gray')
    plt.title(title)
    plt.axis('off')

    plt.subplot(3, 2, 2*i)
    plt.hist(image.ravel(), bins=256, range=[0,255])
    plt.title(f"Histogram of {title}")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

    plot_images_and_histograms(
    [img, stretched_img, hist_eq_img],
    ["Original Image", "Contrast Stretched Image", "Histogram Equalized Image"]
    )
